success.question_text: PLAN is to BUILDER as ___________ is to ACTOR.
success.question_category_path: General Ability / Verbal Reasoning / Analogies

review_1.column_1_text:

success.question_text: Which word has a meaning least like the other three?
success.question_category_path: General Ability / Verbal Reasoning / Odd One Out

review_1.column_1_text:
Explanation

A WAGER is a bet. The words SWINDLE, DEFRAUD and CHEAT mean ‘obtaining something illegally and by deception’.

success.question_category_path: General Ability / Non-Verbal Reasoning / Reasoning

review_1.column_1_text: Solution

review_3.column_1_text:
Each of the tiles consists of a triangle. In each row the triangle is pointed ‘up’ in two cases and ‘down’ in the other case. A circle appears inside the triangle in one tile, a pair of vertical lines appears in another tile, and just the triangle appears in the last tile.

Tip

The matrix consists of nine squares containing shapes which form a pattern. Look along a row, or down a column, to see how each tile is related to the next and use this relationship to find the shapes in the missing tile.

success.question_text:
Which group of letters comes next in this series?

BFD      HLJ      NRP      ______
success.question_category_path: General Ability / Verbal Reasoning / Series

review_1.column_1_text:
Explanation

Each group of three is the first, last and middle letters of a group of five letters in alphabetical order. Each new set is the next group of five with a gap of one letter.

review_1.column_1_text:

success.question_text:
Which two of the following statements together prove that:

COMEDIANS ARE FUNNY?

I. All vaudevillians are funny.

II. Some actors are comedians.

III. All vaudevillians are actors.

IV. Vaudevillians perform on the stage.

V. All vaudevillians are comedians.
success.question_category_path: General Ability / Verbal Reasoning / Logic

review_1.column_1_text:
Explanation

(I and V) All vaudevillians are funny. All vaudevillians are comedians.

success.question_text: Which is the odd one out?
success.question_category_path: General Ability / Non-Verbal Reasoning / Reasoning

review_1.column_1_text: Solution

review_3.column_1_text:
All of the shapes have one diagonal drawn. In three of the shapes a line is drawn from a vertex to meet the diagonal at right angles.

Tip

See how one of the objects is different from the other three.

success.question_text: Which word is the odd one out?
success.question_category_path: General Ability / Verbal Reasoning / Odd One Out

review_1.column_1_text:

success.question_text:
These words run in pairs. Insert the missing word to complete the third pair.

      DECIDE—DECISION
      INTEND—INTENTION
      SECURE— __________
success.question_category_path: General Ability / Verbal Reasoning / Word Skills

review_1.column_1_text:
Explanation

DECIDE, INTEND and SECURE are verbs. DECISION and INTENTION are nouns. The corresponding noun for SECURE is SECURITY. (Note: SECURE can also be an adjective.)
